              <section id='description'>
                <h2>We believe that it should be easy for businesses and individuals to tame real&ndash;time data.</h2>
                <p>
                  We apply machine learning and semantic analysis of natural language to find meaningful trends in the noisy and incomplete data found online. 
                </p>
                <p>
                  Our algorithms are looking for dependable patterns that have predictive power. Our API isolates the signals from the noise, giving our clients real&ndash;time answers to specific questions about their industry and their customers.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Since much online communication is now geo&ndash;tagged, we can visualize patterns on a map and observe interactions between specific individuals. We do this at a large scale and without any active user participation. As a result, we can predict the emergence of global phenomena from people's day&ndash;to&ndash;day activities and interactions.
                </p>
                <p>
                  By augmenting existing data sets with live input from social media, we&rsquo;re able to connect the dots and visualize patterns, and then refine models based on user feedback.
                </p>
                <p>
